Definition of personal data
Pursuant to Article 1 of the DP Law, personal data is defined as any information regardless of their nature, and format, relating to an identified or identifiable person.
Definition of sensitive personal data
Sensitive personal data is defined under the law as personal data which reveal the racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious or philosophical beliefs or union membership of the person concerned or relating to his health, including his genetic data (article 1.3 of the DP Law).Last modified 28 Jan 2019
				
			